latestIgtvVideos.title: High Protein Choco Chunk Cup Cake
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Delicious Choco Chunk High Protein Cup Cake🧁🧁(low carb & No Sugar) 

It is Super Delicious 😋😋! Give it a try and let me know!

Macros as follows: 
Protein- 41 gms
Carbs- 10 gms 
Fats- 20 gms 

Total Calories- 210kal 
-----------------------------
Ingredients: 
1 scoop Iso- whey (vanilla)
1 spoon peanut butter (natural/ without sugar)
1 spoon sugar free dark chocolate (crushed)
2 spoons water 
------------------------------
Recipe:
Step1- Take a microwave safe mug or a glass 
Grease it with drop of oil/ghee 

Step2- Put 1 Scoop of whey on the same glass, any flavor ( preferably vanilla/chocolate) in my case I have added iso- whey (from vitafit nutrition)for cutting down carbs but you can add any whey of your choice..!

Step3- Add 1 spoon Unsweetened Peanut butter or egg ( as per you preference)

Step4- Add crushed sugar free chocolate 🍫 mix it well! 

Step5- Put it in the microwave-oven for around 40- 50 seconds/ if you don't have a oven, take a deep frying pan, put a thin layer of salt and pre- heat the pan for about 40 secs and then place the glass with the batter, cover it with a lid and let it cook for 50 secs.

Step7- Enjoy your delicious and healthy 😋 Protein Cup Cake!! Guilt free! 

#healthylifestyle #vitafitnutrition@vitafit_nutrition @hemann007 @rohitramchandran @onpath_11
 #gurumannnutrition thanks for the recipe @gurumann

My Bhaag Rajveer Bhaag story 🥺

I never used to run. My cardiovascular health was terrible. I was just a fat kid who avoided anything physically demanding. One day, a thief snatched my wallet and ran! 🏃‍♂️ I chased him but collapsed after 500-700 meters. 😫  That moment changed everything. I realized fitness isn't just about looks. It's about being prepared. 💪  From then on, I trained for real-life strength and resilience. 

If you don't want to feel powerless, start now!  Train for life!  DM me if you're ready! 🔥

"Same old story, but a different version of me.

I grew up hearing it all—
"You're too fat."
"You look ugly."
"Maggie valie body."

Fast forward to today, and suddenly, the same people say—
"You look so fit."
"Handsome."
"Smart."
"Hot."

But you know what? The only constant through it all was me—my struggles, my resilience, my journey. My family and true friends stood by me, but most importantly, I learned to stand by myself.

It took time, but I finally accept myself—not because the world does, but because I’ve put in the work, and I know my worth.

If you've ever felt judged, overlooked, or doubted—remember, their words don’t define you. Your actions do.

Drop a 🔥 in the comments if you've ever transformed—physically, mentally, or emotionally! Let’s inspire each other. 💪"
